{{.Description}}

## Tech Stack
- **Language**: Rust (2021 edition)
- **Framework**: Axum 0.8
- **Runtime**: Tokio async
- **Database**: PostgreSQL 17 (via Docker)
- **ORM/Query**: SQLx (compile-time checked)
- **Serialization**: Serde + serde_json

## Project Structure
- `src/main.rs` - Entry point, router setup, server config
- `src/handlers/` - Request handler functions
- `src/models/` - Data structures and database models
- `tests/` - Integration tests
- `docs/supporting/` - Supporting documentation

## Development Commands
```bash
make start    # Start Docker Compose stack
make stop     # Stop all services
make test     # Run tests
make build    # Build project
make run      # Run locally
make check    # Check compilation
make fmt      # Format code
make clippy   # Run linter
```

## Conventions
- Use Axum extractors for request parsing (Json, Path, Query)
- Handlers return `impl IntoResponse`
- Use SQLx for database queries (compile-time checked when possible)
- Error handling with custom error types implementing `IntoResponse`
- Logging via `tracing` crate
- Configuration via environment variables (dotenvy)
- Use `tower` middleware for cross-cutting concerns
